<DOC><DOCNO> AP890418-0070 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-04-18-89 0849EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-China-Quake     04-18 0166</FIRST><SECOND>PM-China-Quake,0172</SECOND><HEAD>Seven Killed By Aftershocks</HEAD><DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Seven people died today in the aftershocks of aserious earthquake that struck a remote southwestern region, thestate-run news agency said.   The initial tremor Sunday, measuring 6.7 on the Richter scale,was centered on Batang county, a mountainous area near Sichuanprovince's western border with Tibet. At least four were reportedkilled.   The official Xinhua News Agency said today's aftershocks killedseven people, injured 37 and destroyed 700 houses. The strongestaftershock measured 4.4 on the Richter scale, Xinhua said.   Communications with Batang were hampered by heavy snow Sundayand disrupted phone lines Monday, the agency said.   It said casualties and damage in neighboring Markam county, aregion inhabited by Tibetans, were not known because roads to theregion were blocked. The Richter scale is a gauge of energyreleased by an earthquake as measured by the ground motion recordedon a seismograph. A quake measuring 6 can cause severe damage in apopulated area.</TEXT></DOC>